WEBVTT

00:02.303 --> 00:04.338
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:28.629 --> 00:31.799
♪♪

00:37.471 --> 00:38.706
Mm.

00:38.739 --> 00:39.740
[ Sighs ]

00:39.773 --> 00:41.075
[ Both groan ]

00:41.109 --> 00:43.244
Weird. It's like nothing
is happening today.

00:43.277 --> 00:46.080
I know. Today's so boring
that if it was a person,

00:46.114 --> 00:47.948
it'd wear a polo shirt
and khakis.

00:47.981 --> 00:49.217
But it's a Saturday.

00:49.250 --> 00:50.984
The possibilities
are endless.

00:51.018 --> 00:52.886
That's the problem with
infinite possibilities --

00:52.920 --> 00:54.322
one of them is
infinite boredom.

00:54.355 --> 00:55.356
[ Both sigh ]

00:55.389 --> 00:58.926
[ Wind whistling ]

00:58.959 --> 01:00.761
What? How did that
even get in here?

01:00.794 --> 01:03.831
Maybe something will happen
if we just wait a little longer.

01:03.864 --> 01:05.366
No, we've already been
sitting here for so long

01:05.399 --> 01:06.734
that your butt
has fossilized.

01:06.767 --> 01:08.436
Come on,
let's get out of here.

01:08.469 --> 01:10.338
[ Metal clanging ]

01:14.775 --> 01:16.644
Mm.

01:16.677 --> 01:18.679
Aren't you coming?

01:18.712 --> 01:19.680
Mine's grown roots.

01:19.713 --> 01:20.748
Oh.

01:20.781 --> 01:22.015
[ Rip! ]

01:22.049 --> 01:23.751
Ooh, you're gonna
have to wax that.

01:23.784 --> 01:25.786
That's okay.
I'll just prune it.

01:25.819 --> 01:27.054
[ Can clanks ]

01:27.087 --> 01:29.257
There's nothing going on
out here either.

01:29.290 --> 01:30.758
[ Screams ]

01:30.791 --> 01:32.426
[ Tires screech ]
[ Crash! ]

01:32.460 --> 01:34.094
Ah, puddles.

01:34.128 --> 01:36.764
Perhaps I should partake in
some infantile joie de vivre

01:36.797 --> 01:38.966
that becomes
a boy of my age.

01:38.999 --> 01:41.602
[ Laughing ]

01:41.635 --> 01:43.070
Blegh!
-I just don't understand.

01:43.103 --> 01:46.607
There has to be something
interesting happening somewhere.

01:46.640 --> 01:49.777
No.
Dude, I'm just saying I think we
should swap every now and then.

01:49.810 --> 01:51.479
I'm always stuck
on the night shift.

01:51.512 --> 01:54.114
It's not fair.
You know you couldn't
handle the day shift.

01:54.148 --> 01:55.483
You're just not
bright enough.

01:55.516 --> 01:57.885
[ Gasps ] Tell me you did not
just say that!

01:57.918 --> 02:00.120
Wait. No.
I-I didn't mean it like that.

02:00.154 --> 02:02.723
It's just that you're not
a -- a star like me.

02:02.756 --> 02:04.958
Oh, so you're
the star of the show

02:04.992 --> 02:06.827
even though I do
half the work, huh?

02:06.860 --> 02:09.363
Well, I'll show you stars,
you giant gas bag!

02:09.397 --> 02:10.831
[ Groans ]

02:10.864 --> 02:13.167
Pbht. Even the weather
is boring.

02:13.201 --> 02:15.269
-[ Grunting ]
-Please stop.

02:15.303 --> 02:17.070
You know very well
that ain't gonna work.

02:17.104 --> 02:19.407
Oh, yeah, why? 'Cause
you're so hot at fighting, too?

02:19.440 --> 02:20.474
No.

02:20.508 --> 02:23.143
Because I'm 95 million miles
away from you.

02:23.177 --> 02:24.978
Yeah, well,
you didn't hit me either,

02:25.012 --> 02:26.914
so let's call it a tie.

02:29.550 --> 02:31.552
[ Rumbling ]

02:31.585 --> 02:32.553
[ Airplane engine whirs ]

02:32.586 --> 02:33.721
[ Clank! ]

02:33.754 --> 02:35.523
[ Crash! ]

02:35.556 --> 02:37.825
[ Munching ]

02:37.858 --> 02:38.826
Huh?

02:38.859 --> 02:40.060
[ Gasps ]

02:40.093 --> 02:41.429
This is an emergency.

02:41.462 --> 02:42.563
We've got a code zero.

02:42.596 --> 02:43.764
There are zero doughnuts left.

02:43.797 --> 02:45.566
I'm going to the doughnut store.

02:45.599 --> 02:49.837
[ Siren wails ]

02:49.870 --> 02:51.038
[ Radio static ]

02:51.071 --> 02:52.406
Chief,
there's a black and white car

02:52.440 --> 02:54.575
speeding out of control
on West Elmore Boulevard.

02:54.608 --> 02:56.644
That guy again, huh?

02:56.677 --> 02:58.111
He's my worst enemy.

02:58.145 --> 03:00.147
That kid that called you
Pinky McHole?

03:00.180 --> 03:01.882
-No, the other one.
-Cholesterol?

03:01.915 --> 03:03.384
No, the 4:00 offender.

03:03.417 --> 03:05.919
But don't worry,
I'll get him this time.

03:05.953 --> 03:07.588
[ Tires screech ]

03:07.621 --> 03:09.657
He took a left
at Fourth and Pico.

03:09.690 --> 03:10.791
[ Tires screech ]

03:10.824 --> 03:12.926
[ Horn honks ]

03:12.960 --> 03:14.828
-Aaah!
[ Tires screech ]

03:15.796 --> 03:18.098
-Aaah!
[ Metal straining ]

03:20.568 --> 03:22.303
[ Sighs ]
[ Clunk! ]

03:22.336 --> 03:24.672
[ Tires screech ]

03:24.705 --> 03:27.875
[ Siren wailing ]

03:27.908 --> 03:29.310
Dude, there's no point
holding your breath.

03:29.343 --> 03:30.744
Nothing interesting's
gonna happen.

03:30.778 --> 03:31.845
[ Gasps ]

03:31.879 --> 03:33.247
[ Crunch! ]

03:33.281 --> 03:34.815
Somehow he's made it
to Seventh Avenue.

03:34.848 --> 03:36.484
This ends today.

03:36.517 --> 03:37.585
[ Engine revs ]

03:37.618 --> 03:39.152
Aaaah!

03:39.186 --> 03:41.221
Okay, you better
find a shortcut.

03:41.255 --> 03:43.824
[ Tires screech ]
-He's heading right.

03:43.857 --> 03:45.926
Now right again.

03:45.959 --> 03:47.295
Now left.

03:47.328 --> 03:48.095
Right.

03:48.128 --> 03:49.763
Left.
Right.

03:49.797 --> 03:51.231
Left.
Right.

03:51.265 --> 03:52.800
Left.
Left.

03:52.833 --> 03:54.502
Right.
Right.

03:54.535 --> 03:55.603
[ Crash! ]

03:55.636 --> 03:57.338
Uh, Chief,
I just figured out

03:57.371 --> 03:58.906
why you can never
catch this guy.

03:58.939 --> 04:01.642
You know, how you always
run out of doughnuts at 4:00?

04:01.675 --> 04:03.744
Not now.
I'm closing in on him.

04:03.777 --> 04:05.446
Okay, sure.

04:05.479 --> 04:06.680
Uh, yeah.

04:06.714 --> 04:08.416
You go get him, sir.

04:08.449 --> 04:09.783
[ Siren wails ]

04:09.817 --> 04:11.485
[ Both gasp ]

04:11.519 --> 04:12.886
Meh. Meh.

04:12.920 --> 04:16.123
Ugh, man, this guy's definitely
collecting for something.

04:16.156 --> 04:17.825
Hi, there. Can I have a minute
of your time?

04:17.858 --> 04:19.493
Nah, hold that thought.

04:23.196 --> 04:25.098
Hi, there.
Can I have minute of your time?

04:25.132 --> 04:26.634
We'd like you to
help us find a use

04:26.667 --> 04:28.636
for a brand-new product
we're developing.

04:28.669 --> 04:29.637
Sure.

04:29.670 --> 04:30.804
[ Zing! ]

04:30.838 --> 04:32.640
[ Whirring ]

04:32.673 --> 04:36.977
[ Gasps ] I know
just what to do with this.

04:37.010 --> 04:39.413
[ Sizzle! ]

04:41.549 --> 04:43.684
Ah, ah, ah, ah!

04:43.717 --> 04:46.019
Oh, oh, oh, oh!

04:46.053 --> 04:48.822
Ah, oh, oh, oh. Ow.

04:48.856 --> 04:51.425
Aaah! Oh, oh, oh.

04:51.459 --> 04:53.327
Ow, oh, ow.

04:53.361 --> 04:54.695
Ohh! Ow!

04:54.728 --> 04:55.996
Ah, ah!

04:56.029 --> 04:57.297
[ Click! ]

05:00.534 --> 05:01.502
[ Sizzle! ]

05:01.535 --> 05:02.936
Can you see any better?

05:02.970 --> 05:04.638
-No.
[ Sizzle! ]

05:04.672 --> 05:06.039
-How about now?
-No.

05:06.073 --> 05:07.040
Any other comments?

05:07.074 --> 05:08.241
[ Squeaking ]

05:08.275 --> 05:11.445
It hurts tremendously.

05:11.479 --> 05:15.916
[ Whooshing ]

05:15.949 --> 05:17.184
I'm not sure if I'm tanning

05:17.217 --> 05:19.186
or it's just
my birthmark spreading.

05:20.320 --> 05:22.289
[ Zing! ]

05:23.791 --> 05:25.292
[ Sizzle! ]

05:26.460 --> 05:28.562
Aah!

05:28.596 --> 05:30.998
[ Sour note plays ]

05:32.533 --> 05:35.603
[ Buzzing ]

05:35.636 --> 05:36.837
Hmm.

05:36.870 --> 05:40.107
♪♪

05:44.211 --> 05:46.213
Guys, I finally
found a use for it.

05:52.185 --> 05:53.521
Here's your reward.

05:53.554 --> 05:54.822
Thanks.

05:54.855 --> 05:58.526
[ Sighs ] Well, now we know this
has no use whatsoever.

05:58.559 --> 06:03.063
Off to the trash with you with
all my other useless inventions.

06:03.096 --> 06:04.164
[ Squeaking ]

06:04.197 --> 06:07.635
Uggghhh!
This day is so boring.

06:09.937 --> 06:11.138
[ Grunting ]

06:11.171 --> 06:13.006
[ Alarm blaring ]

06:13.040 --> 06:15.876
[ Horn honking ]

06:15.909 --> 06:17.110
[ Horn honks ]

06:17.144 --> 06:18.345
[ Grunts ]

06:18.378 --> 06:19.747
[ Gasps ]

06:19.780 --> 06:23.350
[ Alarms, horns continue ]

06:23.383 --> 06:25.486
♪ They say a thumb
can't change his print ♪

06:25.519 --> 06:27.054
♪ But lookin' at
this window's tint ♪

06:27.087 --> 06:28.656
♪ I see the boy I used to be

06:28.689 --> 06:31.525
♪ If he saw me,
what would he see? ♪

06:31.559 --> 06:33.427
♪ He'd look at me in disbelief

06:33.461 --> 06:35.162
♪ A dirty, no-good
thumbprint thief ♪

06:35.195 --> 06:36.630
♪ Forever stealing,
gettin' busted ♪

06:36.664 --> 06:39.399
♪ On the run, or being dusted

06:39.433 --> 06:42.803
♪ But this symphony
of car alarms ♪

06:42.836 --> 06:46.106
♪ Has reminded me
of music's charms ♪

06:46.139 --> 06:49.376
♪ As a boy I dreamed
that I'd go far ♪

06:49.409 --> 06:54.347
♪ As a bona fide musical star

06:54.381 --> 06:57.150
♪ I sung a little song,
did a little show ♪

06:57.184 --> 06:59.520
♪ Got sick of the producers
saying no ♪

06:59.553 --> 07:02.322
♪ So I turned to crime,
stealin' all the time ♪

07:02.355 --> 07:04.825
♪ Life lacked reason,
life lacked rhyme ♪

07:04.858 --> 07:07.394
♪ Now it's time to say
I'm sorry ♪

07:07.427 --> 07:09.763
♪ What better way
than in a song ♪

07:09.797 --> 07:11.364
♪ Give me back
the car you stole ♪

07:11.398 --> 07:12.633
♪ I'll pay you back
in rock 'n' roll ♪

07:12.666 --> 07:14.201
♪ You took my daughter's
trampoline ♪

07:14.234 --> 07:15.603
♪ Well,
how about this tap routine ♪

07:15.636 --> 07:17.404
♪ You stole
my mother's diamond ring ♪

07:17.437 --> 07:25.078
♪ It doesn't really matter
'cause I can si-i-i-ing ♪

07:25.112 --> 07:26.547
[ Groaning ]
[ Alarms blaring ]

07:26.580 --> 07:27.715
No, you can't!

07:27.748 --> 07:29.983
Oh, come on,
it can't be that bad.

07:30.017 --> 07:32.753
Ah, then you only have
yourselves to blame for this.

07:32.786 --> 07:33.854
[ Glass shatters ]

07:33.887 --> 07:34.855
[ Engine revs ]

07:34.888 --> 07:37.024
[ All shouting ]

07:37.057 --> 07:38.526
Darwin: What?

07:38.559 --> 07:41.729
I thought I heard something,
but, eh.

07:42.062 --> 07:43.497
Corn Guy: Good afternoon.

07:43.531 --> 07:47.701
I'm here to tell you about
today's special offer.

07:47.735 --> 07:48.636
[ Splat! ]

07:48.669 --> 07:50.704
There!
Something's gonna happen!

07:51.939 --> 07:53.641
-Oh!
-Aaah!

07:53.674 --> 07:55.075
[ Gasps ]

07:55.108 --> 07:56.677
[ Gags ]

08:00.080 --> 08:02.182
[ Retches forcefully ]

08:02.215 --> 08:06.019
[ Sighs ]

08:06.053 --> 08:07.254
Aaah!

08:07.287 --> 08:12.392
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

08:12.425 --> 08:14.294
[ Squish! ]
-Aaaah!

08:14.327 --> 08:15.796
Good afternoon.

08:15.829 --> 08:18.065
I'm here to tell you about
today's special offer.

08:18.098 --> 08:21.669
Two bottles of detergent
for the price of one and a half.

08:21.702 --> 08:24.838
[ Laughs ]
Did you guys see that?

08:24.872 --> 08:25.939
No. No.

08:25.973 --> 08:27.040
Oh,
don't worry about it.

08:27.074 --> 08:28.075
I got it on my phone.

08:28.108 --> 08:29.376
[ Both gasp ]

08:29.409 --> 08:32.345
[ Laughing ]

08:32.379 --> 08:34.514
Dude, you had it
on the face camera.

08:34.548 --> 08:36.884
Yeah, but you could really
tell how good it was

08:36.917 --> 08:38.886
by how much I'm laughing.

08:38.919 --> 08:40.788
What do we do now?

08:40.821 --> 08:42.422
We're going home
to watch the clock

08:42.455 --> 08:44.825
until this hideous day
finally ends.

08:50.430 --> 08:52.966
Yeah, I'm pretty sure
this is the one.

08:53.000 --> 08:55.268
[ Truck beeping ]

08:55.736 --> 08:59.206
♪♪

08:59.239 --> 09:00.941
[ Clock ticks ]
-Ugh!

09:00.974 --> 09:04.044
[ Raspy ] Why does time only
slow down when you're bored?

09:04.077 --> 09:05.579
[ Engine rumbling ]

09:08.215 --> 09:09.717
[ Static ]

09:14.855 --> 09:17.825
Hi Five: Hi Five Ghost,
ride the whip. [ Chuckles ]

09:17.858 --> 09:20.327
Hi Five Ghost, ride the -- oh.
[ Splash! ]

09:20.360 --> 09:22.630
[ Static ]

09:22.663 --> 09:24.364
Uncle Grandpa: Good morning!
[ Crash! ]

09:24.397 --> 09:26.266
-Oh.
-Good morning.

09:26.299 --> 09:28.902
[ Static ]

09:31.839 --> 09:34.374
You know, it's funny,
but in this picture,

09:34.407 --> 09:35.876
the house
looks kind of pink.

09:35.909 --> 09:38.445
Uh-huh, matches the one
we got on the back.

09:38.478 --> 09:40.247
No,
the one we got is blue.

09:40.280 --> 09:41.782
Uh, no, that's blue.

09:41.815 --> 09:45.152
Just like the frosting
on this doughnut.

09:45.185 --> 09:46.486
You're colorblind,
aren't you?

09:46.519 --> 09:47.988
-Hm?
[ Turn signal clicking ]

09:49.957 --> 09:51.258
Cotton candy?

09:51.291 --> 09:53.861
-Also pink.
-No!

09:55.262 --> 09:58.098
♪♪

09:58.131 --> 10:01.168
[ Doorbell rings ]

10:02.102 --> 10:05.706
Is this the dwelling where I
shall find two brave strangers

10:05.739 --> 10:09.677
to help me on my quest
that will be perilous?

10:09.710 --> 10:12.545
We will go to places
man has never dared tread.

10:12.579 --> 10:18.151
But above all, it will be
the journey of a lifetime!

10:18.185 --> 10:20.520
You're in luck,
little man.

10:20.553 --> 10:22.122
We know just who you need.

10:22.155 --> 10:25.225
Yeah, there's these two geeks
who are really into role-play.

10:25.258 --> 10:26.526
They'd be perfect for it.

10:26.559 --> 10:28.295
They live two blocks down
on the left.

10:28.328 --> 10:30.731
Oh, you sure you two wouldn't --
Oh!

10:31.531 --> 10:32.700
[ Both gasp ]

10:32.733 --> 10:34.935
Both: Wait!

10:34.968 --> 10:35.936
Those two guys!

10:35.969 --> 10:37.838
Oh,
you've had second thoughts.

10:37.871 --> 10:40.340
Yeah. They're not two blocks
on the left.

10:40.373 --> 10:41.775
They're two blocks
on the right.

10:41.809 --> 10:44.077
Oh, all right, whatever.
Thanks.

10:45.078 --> 10:46.980
I guess we learned something
today, Darwin.

10:47.014 --> 10:48.782
Life doesn't come knocking
at your door.

10:48.816 --> 10:50.583
It's down to you
to make things happen.

10:50.617 --> 10:52.019
Shall we
get on with it then?

10:52.052 --> 10:54.755
Nah, I'm not much of a doer.
I'm more of a moaner.

10:57.791 --> 10:59.426
Whoo!

10:59.459 --> 11:01.862
[ Laughter ]

11:04.898 --> 11:08.135
♪♪
